measure.CatchLine: Exempts certain projects for public works, primarily related to affordable housing, from the requirement to pay a prevailing rate of wage.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Digest: Says that a public agency does not need to set a certain wage level for a project that is affordable housing. (Flesch Readability Score: 60.6). 
	Exempts certain projects for public works, primarily related to affordable housing, from the requirement to pay a prevailing rate of wage. 
	Takes effect on the 91st day following adjournment sine die.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to the prevailing rate of wage; creating new provisions; amending ORS 279C.810; and prescribing an effective date.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to the prevailing rate of wage; prescribing an effective date.
measure.FiscalImpact: May have fiscal impact, but no statement yet issued
measure.RevenueImpact: May have revenue impact, but no statement yet issued

historyActions.ActionText: Introduction and first reading. Referred to President's desk.
